Reasoning: The paper deals with optimization algorithms and strategies for a vehicle routing problem with stochastic and time-constrained customer demands, which involves machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for predicting demand probabilities and optimizing routes. The paper also proposes a new public benchmark for the problem, which involves data structures and algorithms for handling large-scale instances. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics and Control), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
